zoomSelected(25.10)                                        zoomSelected(25.10)

Name
       zoomSelected  -  Zooms in the viewable window to the area that encloses
       the selected objects

Syntax
       zoomSelected

       [-help]

       [-margin <value>]

       Zooms in the viewable window to the area that encloses the selected ob-
       jects.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the zoomSelected command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man  command:
              man zoomSelected.

       -margin <value>
              Specifies  the  zoom margin ratio as an integral value. The zoom
              margin is the minimum spacing between the bounding  box  of  the
              selected object(s) and the layout view.

              The minimum value is 0 and the maximum value is 99.

              Default: 50

